  "raw_meta_yaml": "schema_version: 1\n\ncontext:\n  version: \"0.10.0\"\n\npackage:\n  name: mmgpy\n  version: ${{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  url: https://github.com/kmarchais/mmgpy/archive/refs/tags/v${{ version }}.tar.gz\n  sha256: 4d74a8cbd49d5073c322f3a5b187b92fed1c855668b9bede567b155523d78b84\n\nbuild:\n  number: 0\n  script:\n    - if: unix\n      then: |\n        cmake -B build ${CMAKE_ARGS} -DMMGPY_CONDA_BUILD=ON -DBUILD_TESTING=OFF -GNinja\n        cmake --build build\n        cmake --install build\n    - if: win\n      then: |\n        cmake -B build %CMAKE_ARGS% -DMMGPY_CONDA_BUILD=ON -DBUILD_TESTING=OFF -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=\"%PREFIX%;%LIBRARY_PREFIX%\" -GNinja\n        if errorlevel 1 exit 1\n        cmake --build build\n        if errorlevel 1 exit 1\n        cmake --install build\n        if errorlevel 1 exit 1\n\nrequirements:\n  build:\n    - ${{ compiler('c') }}\n    - ${{ compiler('cxx') }}\n    - ${{ stdlib(\"c\") }}\n    - cmake >=3.15\n    - ninja\n  host:\n    - python\n    - pybind11 >=3.0.0\n    - numpy\n    - mmgsuite\n  run:\n    - python\n    - numpy >=2.0.2\n    - meshio >=5.3.5\n    - pyvista >=0.47.0\n    - rich >=13.0.0\n    - scipy >=1.11.0,<2\n    - mmgsuite\n    - if: python < '3.11'\n      then: typing-extensions >=4.0.0\n\ntests:\n  - python:\n      imports:\n        - mmgpy\n        - mmgpy._mmgpy\n  - script:\n      - if: unix\n        then:\n          # MMG -h returns exit code 2; just verify executables are on PATH\n          - mmg3d_O3 -h || test $? -eq 2\n          - mmg2d_O3 -h || test $? -eq 2\n          - mmgs_O3 -h || test $? -eq 2\n          - python -c \"from mmgpy._mmgpy import MmgMesh3D; m = MmgMesh3D(); print('MmgMesh3D OK')\"\n      - if: win\n        then:\n          - mmg3d_O3.exe -h || ver >nul\n          - mmg2d_O3.exe -h || ver >nul\n          - mmgs_O3.exe -h || ver >nul\n          - python -c \"from mmgpy._mmgpy import MmgMesh3D; m = MmgMesh3D(); print('MmgMesh3D OK')\"\n\nabout:\n  homepage: https://github.com/kmarchais/mmgpy\n  license: MIT\n  license_file: LICENSE\n  summary: Python bindings for the MMG mesh generation/optimization library\n  description: |\n    mmgpy provides Python bindings for the MMG library, enabling 2D, 3D,\n    and surface mesh remeshing through both a Python API and CLI tools.\n  repository: https://github.com/kmarchais/mmgpy\n\nextra:\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - kmarchais\n",
